===Etymology===
From the Germanic root ''*blada-'' "leaf", related (via an Indo-European root) to {{Gr.}} ''phyllon'', {{L.}} ''[[folium]].
===Noun===
'''Blatt''' ''n'' (''plural'' '''[[Blätter]]''')
# [[leaf]], [[petal]]
# [[piece]] of [[paper]]
#:''Auf dem Blatt steht nichts drauf.'' - There is nothing written on this piece of paper.
# the [[card]]s of a [[card game]]
#:''Zeig mir dein '''Blatt'''.'' - Show me your cards.

